Toy-maker Fisher-Price is recalling 83 toys, including popular characters like Big Bird and Elmo, due to excessive lead paint.
This is the first recall for Fisher-Price and parent company Mattel.
Mattel's CEO apologized for the recall, which will impact operating income by $30 million.
Concerns over Chinese-made products have parents worried, with 80% of toys made in China.
The recall has sparked calls for stricter safety measures.
RC2, the manufacturer of Thomas & Friends toys, is conducting lead testing on all paint batches.
Mattel has halted operations at the factory responsible for the lead paint and initiated an investigation.
